	   <a name=9758951363450></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9758951363450><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj>The Holy Swords (rant of sorts)</span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=3038><span id= >Rilen</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>4 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Dec 4th 1:59 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hail and Well Met, Friends.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;  <br>Admittedly, I'm fairly aged in terms of the game (I started last October and quit before Kunark), so my thoughts are largely reminescient, but even so, I am wont to hate all that the fetid continent of Kunark has brought the game. The player-run economy is nothing like it was in my day, with every blade and article of armor that I remember being of little to no worth in comparison to those that the fetid continent has brought upon us. I remember the days when a GhoulBane was worth five-thousand plat, the mithril breastplate ten to fifteen. The blades that have been added do not coincide with the game's former atmosphere, and I believe do in fact subtract from its current atmosphere.  However, I've rambled long enough over that.<br>     <br>My rant is over the formerly envied, currently overly hyped Holy Swords. With my paladin of old,  you could identify a paladin solely by their blade. We had the best blades in the game, excepting the ultra rare blades from the Planes and GM events. However, since I returned to the game, I have noticed that GhoulBane has dropped in price drastically, and no one even attempts the SoulFire unless they hope for the Fiery Avenger or Fiery Defender.  I fear I am wont to hate the blade christened the Fiery Defender, but not because of stats or its horrid proc, but because of its appearance, which I fear further degrades the atmosphere of the game.<br><br>The blade's hilt admittedly, is quite nice, albeit unwieldy. However, the blade, which others have complimented for being more impressive than others, is in my eyes rather hideous.  The traditional conotation of a paladin is a knight in the service of Christendom which leads one to believe their blades would be of a traditional European styling, but, due to the flames being so close and thick one can only fail to see the blade, it appears to be of a Moorish flamberge styling. That, I believe (as one obsessed with appearance), is a personal affront to the now degraded atmosphere of paladins. Also, the flames are of a darker orangish tint than SoulFire's, making it harder to believe it to be holy fire enveloping the blade. In my opinion, the blade of the Fiery Defender continues to ruin the atmosphere of the paladin.<br><br>Please my friends, do not consider this whining. I'm quite happy in the game, and I enjoy the quest as well as any. I just...I just had to get this off my chest. Ever since I have returned, I've seen more and more that confirms the fears of my friends of long ago. The game has lost nigh all of its atmosphere, and in its place is a desire to do the unwieldy. I guess I just miss the EverQuest of old...*sigh*<br>   <br>Friends, my apologies for wasting your time;  I hope I have not offended and I hope I have not dissapointed. Also, although the atmosphere of this board is friendly enough, please understand it has been a great long while since I posted on a board so please don't rip me apart...*smiles weakly* <br><br>My friends, enjoy the blades of your era as I do mine.<br><br>Rilen Draconigena<br>Confessor of 22 Truths (in this life of Rilen)<br>Humble Servant of Marr<br>Servant of Congregatio Et Iustitia<br>-The Rathe-<br><br>(edit: D'oh! Friends, I fear I have erred, in that is a strategies board.  I had come to accept this board as a paladin message board.  My humble apologies.)<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
